annotationA: Glycine cleavage system P protein; The glycine cleavage system catalyzes the degradation of glycine
annotationB: Glycine N-methyltransferase catalyzes the methylation reaction of glycine to generate sarcosine (N-methylglycine).  It is abundantly expressed in the fat body and controls the amount of methyl donor S-adenosylmethionine (SAM); Belongs to the class I-like SAM-binding methyltransferase superfamily. Glycine N-methyltransferase family
